description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Performance Analysis Team is an analytical service supporting NHS England and NHS Improvement national and regional teams by providing information and analysis to inform policy and operational decisions. Our service spans the whole analytical pipeline, from data development and data collection, through to reporting and bespoke analysis. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Example projects include: &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Modelling to inform Spending Review discussions with the Department of Health and Her Majesty’s Treasury&lt;br /&gt;In-depth analysis to shape the Long-Term Plan&lt;br /&gt;Collecting and assuring plans to ensure that local health systems can deliver the care their patients need within the resources they have available&lt;br /&gt;Monitoring in-year delivery and working with local health systems to improve performance &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Our staff operate from Leeds, London and regional offices. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Marcus Albano&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Deputy Director of Analytics - South West&lt;/p&gt;
